  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kechene Water, Sanitation and Hygiene Promotion Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Construction of water kiosks and communal water tankers.

Five water and sanitation committees established and trained on water/sanitation facility management, financial management, operation and maintenance, personal hygiene, sanitation/ environmental sanitation, communicable diseases, eye disease, how to develop by-law, fee system and solid/liquid waste management.

42 (all female) members of solid waste management from 6 organized groups   receive training on personal hygiene, sanitation, solid and liquid waste management, how to prevent WASH related communicable diseases and how to generate income from wastes. The groups also receive equipment such as heavy duty gloves, mask, shovels and carts.    

Establishing and building-capacity for two school hygiene clubs and conduct hygiene and sanitation promotion activities including health education and hygiene promotion  performed by hygiene promoters and community animators.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">It is estimated that nearly three-fourths of health-related problems in Kechene slum are attributable to communicable diseases resulting from unsafe or unhygienic  water and scarce water supply, poor sanitation environment and poor personal hygiene practices. 

The overall goal of this project is to contribute to the reduction of diarrheal diseases and sickness caused by water, poor environmental sanitation and poor hygiene.</narrative>
  </description>
